        "explanation": "Under the Mughal mansabdari system, there were 33 classes. They were given mashrut, that is, conditional ranks. In the 40th regnal year of Akbar, the dual system of zat and sawar was introduced. In this system, the sawar rank could never be higher than the zat rank. In this arrangement, civil and military officers belonged to the same service cadre, and all executive and military officers were granted mansabs.",
