        "explanation": "In history, Sikkim’s connection with India in this context can be seen on three occasions– 1. During the tenure of Lord Hastings, the Treaty of Titalia was concluded between Sikkim and British India on 10 February 1817. It mentioned the restoration of certain territories to Sikkim from Nepal, but there was no mention of the merger of any part of Sikkim into British India. 2. Darjeeling and some part of the Terai of Sikkim were annexed to British India in 1850 during the tenure of Lord Dalhousie. This was a partial annexation of Sikkim. 3. In 1975, Sikkim was fully merged into independent India. In the present question, the Commission determined its answer on the basis of the partial annexation of Sikkim into British India during Lord Dalhousie’s tenure. Therefore, the correct answer is option (c).",
