        "explanation": "The Ryotwari Settlement was a system introduced by the British in India for the collection of land revenue. Alexander Read first implemented the Ryotwari system in 1792 in the Baramahal region of Tamil Nadu in the Madras Presidency. Thomas Munro applied it in some areas in 1809. When he became the Governor of Madras in 1820, he extended it in Madras. Munro’s disciple Elphinstone introduced it in the Bombay Presidency. This system was implemented over about 51 percent of the total area of British India, including Madras, parts of Bombay, Eastern Bengal, Assam. Under this arrangement, the ryots were given ownership rights over the land, and they were directly responsible for paying land revenue. After 1836, improvements were made in this system by Wingate and Goldsmith.",
