        "source": "explanation of (A) explanation of (A) U.P.P.C.S. (Pre) 2020",
        "explanation": "The British Government introduced different land-revenue systems in different parts of India. These systems were the Permanent Settlement, the Ryotwari system, and the Mahalwari system. The Permanent Settlement was implemented in Bengal, Bihar, Odisha, and the Banaras region of Uttar Pradesh. It covered about 19 percent of the total area of British India. The Ryotwari system, covering about 51 percent of the area, was implemented in Madras, parts of Bombay, Eastern Bengal, Assam, and Coorg. The Mahalwari system, covering about 30 percent of the area, was implemented in the United Provinces, the Central Provinces, and Punjab, with some modifications. These separate land-revenue systems in different regions gave rise to different classes among Indian peasants. Therefore, both the Assertion and the Reason are true, and Reason (R) is the correct explanation of Assertion (A).",
