        "disputed": false,
        "source": "U.P.P.C.S. (Mains) 2013",
        "explanation": "The British government passed the Regulating Act of 1773 to remove the corruption and maladministration prevailing in the Company. Under this Act, the Madras and Bombay Presidencies were brought under the Calcutta Presidency. The Governor of Bengal was thereafter called the Governor- General. Warren Hastings was appointed the first Governor- General of Bengal.",
        "bonus": ""
