        "disputed": false,
        "source": "U.P.P.C.S. (Pre) 1998",
        "explanation": "By the Regulating Act of 1773, a Supreme Court was established for the first time at Calcutta. It consisted of one Chief Justice and three other judges. This Supreme Court was to function as a general court, a court under the law of the land, a court of admiralty, and an ecclesiastical court. This Supreme Court was constituted in 1774, and Elijah Impey was appointed as its Chief Justice, while Robert Chambers, Stephen Caesar Le Maistre, and John Hyde were appointed as the other judges.",
        "bonus": ""
