        "disputed": false,
        "source": "U.P. U.D.A./L.D.A. (Spl) (Mains) 2010",
        "explanation": "The Montagu-Chelmsford Report, 1918, recommended that Indian participation in the administration should be increased. The report also recommended that the Civil Services Examination should be conducted simultaneously in England and India and that one-third of the higher civil posts should be reserved for Indians. It was on the basis of the recommendations of the Montagu-Chelmsford Report that, from 1922, the Civil Services Examination began to be held simultaneously in England and India. In its report submitted in 1887, the Aitchison Commission had recommended that the Civil Services Examination should not be conducted simultaneously in England and India.",
