        "source": "U.P.P.C.S. (Pre.) 2023",
        "explanation": "After the Government of India Act, 1919 received British royal assent, provision was made for a 120-member “Chamber of Princes” for the Indian princely states through the proclamation issued by British King George V on 23 December 1919. It was inaugurated in February 1921.",
        "bonus": ""
