        "source": "U.P. P.S.C. (GIC) 2010 ; U.P. Lower Sub. (Pre) 2015",
        "explanation": "The Government of India Act, 1919 provided that the constitutional situation should be reviewed after every ten years. This process was started in 1927, and in this connection the Simon Commission was appointed. The Simon Commission Report, the results of the Round Table Conferences, and the White Paper issued by the British Government formed the basis of the Government of India Act, 1935.",
